# What Is a Neuron

## Learning Objectives
- Understand the basic structure of a neuron.
- Identify the main components of a neuron and their functions.
- Recognize the role of neurons in transmitting information.

## Beat Markers
1. Introduction to Neurons (0:00 - 2:00)
   - Definition of a neuron
   - Importance of neurons in the nervous system
2. Structure of a Neuron (2:00 - 5:00)
   - Cell body (soma)
   - Dendrites
   - Axon
3. Functions of Neuron Components (5:00 - 8:00)
   - Role of the cell body
   - Role of dendrites in receiving signals
   - Role of axons in transmitting signals
4. Conclusion and Recap (8:00 - 10:00)
   - Summary of key points
   - Q&A session

## Cognitive Load
- Low to Medium

## Pacing
- Introduction: 2 minutes
- Structure: 3 minutes
- Functions: 3 minutes
- Conclusion: 2 minutes